The paper deals with image super-resolution using convolutional neural networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning wavelet coefficients of four sub-bands jointly, which is a technique used in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of clique structures, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
